name: Nike Dunk Low “Viotech” DS
description:
Originally released in 2002, the Nike Dunk Low “Viotech” features a crazy quilt of colors that still has the power to divide sneaker collectors. This retro looks to be almost entirely faithful to the original — down to the grey laces and purple outsole — with the only revisions appearing at the black leather tongue and lining. The Viotechs are heralded among sneaker aficionados for their part in the Dunk explosion of the early aughts, and even if the attention-grabbing aesthetic isn’t your cup of tea, there’s no denying they’re a part of recent sneaker history.
